    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-22T03:41:12+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-22T03:41:12+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-21T18:11:12Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-21T18:11:12Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system east of Tasmania will maintain a ridge over SA this week. A cold front is expected to weaken and slide across southern coasts during today. A second cold front may pass over the south again on Saturday with a high pressure system to follow over waters south of the Bight on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones. Marine forecasts are also available on VHF and HF radio. View the radio schedule on www.bom.gov.au/marine</text>
                <text type="postamble">Check the latest Coastal Waters Forecasts for information on wind, wave and weather conditions for neighbouring coastal zones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_MW008" description="South Central Coast" type="coast" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-22T03:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-23T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-21T17:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-22T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast_winds">Southwesterly 10 to 15 knots, reaching up to 20 knots inshore early in the morning. Winds turning southeasterly in the late afternoon.</text>
                <text type="forecast_seas">Around 1 metre.</text>
                <text type="forecast_swell1">Southwesterly 2 metres, increasing to 2 to 3 metres during the afternoon.</text>
                <text type="forecast_weather">The chance of a thunderstorm early this morning. Mostly sunny afternoon.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-23T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-24T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-22T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-23T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast_winds">Easterly 10 to 15 knots turning north to northeasterly during the morning. Winds reaching up to 20 knots west of Kangaroo Island in the late evening.</text>
                <text type="forecast_seas">Around 1 metre.</text>
                <text type="forecast_swell1">Southwesterly 2.5 to 3 metres.</text>
                <text type="forecast_weather">Sunny.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-24T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-23T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast_winds">Northerly 15 to 20 knots.</text>
                <text type="forecast_seas">1 to 1.5 metres.</text>
                <text type="forecast_swell1">Southwesterly 2 to 2.5 metres.</text>
                <text type="forecast_weather">Partly cloudy.</text>
